  "title": "Day 1 (27 January 2026)",
  "body": " Day 1 (27 January 2026)   This is an outline of the topics we covered in the first week of class.      Tudesday 1\/27  Today's agenda:  Welcome  Roll: pronunciation, name corrections  Name plates  Introductions: basics followed by questions from the class  you  me    What this course is about.  New mathematics      Introductions  In pairs, you will be introduced to the class by your partner, and then you will introduce your partner.  Your introduction should include:  your name,  your major,  where you're from,  your favorite hooy or hobbies, and  something you did over break that nobody else in class did.   Once you're introduction is over, Miller will give class a chance to ask you any follow-up questions.  It's hard to come up with a question to ask in front of other people. I will be asking you to do this every day and every week this semester. Today gives you an opportunity to practice this skill.  When student introductions are done, Miller will introduce himself and you will give a chance to ask him questions.    What this course is about  This course is about filling the details that support the Calculus.  We basically go back over important results from Calculus I-III and put them on a rigorous mathematical foundation.  What characteristic or characteristics defines the academic discipline of mathematics?  In mathematics, rigor refers to solid mathematical proof.  Reading, creating, and writing proofs will be a central part of this course.    "
